6 "(3) A health coverage plan renewed, delivered, or issued for delivery in this state
7 shall not deny coverage for GLP-1 medications if all of the following apply:
8 (a) The GLP-1 medication has been approved by the United States Food and Drug
9 Administration regardless of the insured's specific medical condition or diagnosis.
10 (b) The GLP-1 medication is prescribed by a licensed healthcare provider.
11 (c) The GLP-1 medication is on the insurer's formulary or preferred drug list, if
12 applicable.
13 (4) The GLP-1 medication may be subject to annual deductibles, coinsurance, and
14 copayment provisions as are consistent with those established under the health coverage
15 plan.
16 (5) A health coverage plan shall pay twenty-five percent of the cost of covered GLP-
17 1 medications after all discounts and policy benefits are applied when prescribed by a
18 licensed healthcare provider, regardless of the medication's form."
